<!-- Services -->
<section id="services">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row">
            <div class="col-lg-12 text-center">
                <h2 class="section-heading">About</h2>
                <h3 class="section-subheading text-muted" id="aboutText">
                    For many teachers/professors, the struggle to get practical feedback on lectures, lesson plans, 
                    and student comprehension relies on delayed tests and spotty individual feeback. However, the 
                    opportunity to receive real-time tracking of student understanding offers a revolution for proactive 
                    lecturers. EvaluChart allows students to indicate understanding via individual app interfaces with 
                    real-time tracking and questions displayed to the lecturer on a graphing interface.
                </h3>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="row text-center">
            <div class="col-md-4">
                <span class="fa-stack fa-4x">
                    <i class="fa fa-circle fa-stack-2x text-primary"></i>
                    <i class="fa fa-users fa-stack-1x fa-inverse"></i>
                </span>
                <h4 class="service-heading">Assists Lecturers</h4>
                <p class="text-muted" id="textcolumn">
                All too often, teachers stare at a sea of blank faces wondering if the concepts they are 
                teaching are sinking in. Real-time tracking allows lecturers to maximize the amount of time 
                spent on introducing or reinforcing important material and less wasted time covering concepts 
                already understood. </p>
            </div>
            <div class="col-md-4">
                <span class="fa-stack fa-4x">
                    <i class="fa fa-circle fa-stack-2x text-primary"></i>
                    <i class="fa fa-thumbs-o-up fa-stack-1x fa-inverse"></i>
                </span>
                <h4 class="service-heading">Gives Students A Voice</h4>
                <p class="text-muted" id="textcolumn">                
                Particularly in large auditoriums or for those with shy personalities, students can become 
                easily lost without a channel for voicing feedback. EvaluChart offers each individual student 
                the chance to be heard without embarassment or disruption of the natural flow of the lecture. </p>
            </div>
            <div class="col-md-4">
                <span class="fa-stack fa-4x">
                    <i class="fa fa-circle fa-stack-2x text-primary"></i>
                    <i class="fa fa-line-chart fa-stack-1x fa-inverse"></i>
                </span>
                <h4 class="service-heading">Data Analysis</h4>
                <p class="text-muted" id="textcolumn">
                Educators will be able to easily understand what is happening in their class as they progress 
                through the curriculum. Reviewing lecture charts allows for modifications in teaching 
                methods. The application also allows for easy tracking of student attendance to maximize useful 
                class time. </p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

